<h2 id="freedom-case">The Medical Freedom Case: Why Critics Say the FDA Went Too Far</h2>

<p>The counter-arguments to the FDA's position are substantial, and they come from physicians, pharmacists, patients, and legal scholars â€” not just from wellness influencers and supplement companies.</p>

<h3>The Procedural Argument: The FDA Broke Its Own Rules</h3>

<p>This was the core of the Evexias lawsuit and it succeeded. The FDA placed 17 peptides in Category 2 in September 2023 without following the legally required steps: no public comment period, no Pharmacy Compounding Advisory Committee review, no published safety data supporting the specific restrictions. As the Alliance for Pharmacy Compounding stated in a letter to the FDA:</p>

