<h3>Questions to Ask Before Using Any Peptide</h3>

<p>Regardless of where you stand on the FDA vs. medical freedom debate, these questions apply to everyone:</p>

<p><strong>1. Does this peptide have any human clinical data?</strong> Not animal studies, not mechanism-of-action rationale, not testimonials â€” actual controlled human trials. For most wellness peptides, the honest answer is no or very limited. That doesn't necessarily mean they don't work, but it means you're accepting uncertainty about both efficacy and safety.</p>

