<p><strong>3. Is a physician overseeing my use?</strong> Self-administering peptides based on Reddit protocols and TikTok videos removes all medical accountability. A physician can monitor bloodwork, adjust dosing, screen for contraindications, and manage side effects. This applies even if you philosophically support patient autonomy â€” having expert oversight doesn't mean surrendering your decision-making authority.</p>

